        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>9300 and 9400 Models with Cummins N-14 engines built between July, 1996 and May 14, 1997 may have
                    fan drive and pulley misalignment. This condition can cause the fan belt to run off the pulleys. To
                    remedy this, spacer washers are used to reposition the accessory drive pulley, the fan drive
                    mounting bracket bolts are changed, and the bracket is aligned.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
