        <svcproc svcproctype="afcrepair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the fan and refrigerant compressor belt tension.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the belts from the pulleys.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the six accessory drive pulley mounting bolts and remove the pulley from the
                    engine (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9790201">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9790201" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g9790201" filename="../afcfigures/g9790201.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Remove Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert each of the removed mounting bolts (6) into the pulley mounting holes and install
                    a spacer washer, Part Number 2501471C1, onto each pulley mounting bolt. Slide the spacer washer
                    against the back face of the pulley.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>A light coating of grease will help hold the spacer washers in place against the pulley.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the accessory pulley onto the drive flange and tighten the mounting bolts to
                    35 ft-lbs. (47 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Before installing the belts, the fan drive mounting bracket must be aligned.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="align" graphiccount="1">
            <title>FAN DRIVE BRACKET ALIGNMENT</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the fan drive mounting bracket. Remove the stamped bracket and compressor coolant
                    hose as required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two flange head mounting bolts (1/2-20 UNF x 1-1/2 inch) and replace with two
                    hex head bolts, Part Number 80295R1, and lockwashers, Part Number 120384. Install the bolts to a
                    snug, finger tight position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold the bracket firmly against the engine (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9790202">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9790202" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g9790202" filename="../afcfigures/g9790202.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Brackets</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the left bolt (driver's side) first while holding the bracket firmly against the
                    engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the bolts to 70 to 80 ft-lbs. (95 to 109 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the compressor coolant hose if removed.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the upper stamped bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9790202">Figure 2</hotlnk>). Tighten the mounting bolts to 50 ft-lbs. (68 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the refrigerant compressor belt. Tighten the belt to 100 lbs. belt tension.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the fan belt to determine if it can be re-used. If replacement is required, use
                    the correct part number.
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">9300 Model: 3513716C1</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">9400 Model: 3501266C1</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the fan belt to 250 to 300 lbs. for new belts, 200 to 250 lbs. for used belts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Run the engine for 5 minutes, recheck the belt tension, and correct as required.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
